
  Name:  logb
  
  #include <math.h>
  float logbf(float num);
  double logb(double num);
  long double logbl(long double num);
  
  The logb( ) family of functions returns the exponent of num.
  This value is returned as a floating-point integer value.
  A domain error is possible when num is zero.
  logb( ), logbf( ), and logbl( ) were added by C99.
  
  Related Function:  ilogb

